Method Detail

created

boolean created()
Called by the interception container once a new module is created. For future use when a pool of modules is maintained by the container. Should be called once per the lifetime of the module.

Returns:
boolean to indicate that all creation-related processing are completed in case a chain of agents may be implemented by the container. A true value indicates that no further creation-related work is needed.

initialized

boolean initialized(ISmModuleContext context)
Called by the interception container to initialize the module with specific context information so that the module can initialize various states.
This may be called many times during the life-time of a modul whenever there are changes in the context.

Parameters:
context - a reference to a context structure TBD.
Returns:
boolean to indicate that all initialization-related processing are completed in case a chain of activities may be implemented by the container. A true value indicates that no further initialization-related work is needed.

reset

boolean reset()
Resets state of the module to an initialization type of state.

Returns:
boolean to indicate that all resetting-related processing are completed in case a chain of activities may be implemented by the container. A true value indicates that no further resetting-related work is needed.

invoke

boolean invoke(IOntologyHandle sourceOntology,
               IInputModelHandle sourceModel,
               IOntologyHandle targetOntology,
               IRulesHandle mediationRules,
               IOutputModelHandle targetModel)
               throws MediationException
Answers true if all mediation has been completed by this method execution. A false result will mean that a chain of invocations may be applied by the container in case such policy is implemented.

Parameters:
sourceOntology - OntologyHandle for the input (source) ontology model.
sourceModel - ModelHandle for the (input) Model to be mediated.
targetOntology - OntologyHandle for the output (target) ontology model.
mediationRules - OntologyHandle for the ontology containing rules to govern the mediation.
targetModel - ModelHandle for the (output) Model of the mediated input model.
Returns:
boolean to indicate if (true) further processing is required in a chain of mediators (in case the container implements such an option.
Throws:
MediationException

               IInputModelHandle sourceModel,
               IOutputModelHandle targetModel)
               throws MediationException
Parameters:
ontologyLocator - an OntologyLocator is a facility to locate ontologies in a repository that is shared among mediators to facilitate reuse or computing resources and improve overall efficiency of the container.
sourceModel - ModelHandle for the (input) Model to be mediated.
targetModel - ModelHandle for the (output) Model of the mediated input model.
Returns:
boolean to indicate if (true) further processing is required in a chain of mediators (in case the container implements such an option.
Throws:
MediationException

tearDown

boolean tearDown()
Kills the resources used by this module in case the container implements a pool of modules so that this module can release all its allocated resources.
Can be called only once at the end of the lifetime of a module.

Returns:
boolean to indicate that all tear-down-related activities are done in case the interception container implements a chain of activities.

close

boolean close()
Resets the module back to an inactive state that needs to be initialized before use.
Can be called multiple times during lifetime of a module.

Returns:
boolean to indicate that all close-related activities are done in case the interception container implements a chain of activities.
